-- Gallinari Scores 37 as Nuggets Defeat Knicks 119-114 in Double Overtime
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-01-22T05:18:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/gallinari-scores-37-as-nuggets-defeat-knicks-119-114-in-double-overtime.html
Danilo Gallinari scored 37 points to
lead the  Denver Nuggets  to a 119-114 victory over the  New York 
Knicks in double overtime in a National Basketball Association
contest.  Gallinari scored nine of the Nuggets’ 14 points in the
second overtime for the win at New York’s Madison Square Garden.  During regulation play, Gallinari hit two free throws to
give the Nuggets a 98-96 lead with seven seconds left in the
fourth quarter.  Carmelo Anthony  sunk a 23-foot jumper with one
second left to tie the game. Denver’s Al Harrington missed a 26-
foot 3-pointer at the buzzer to force the first overtime.  Anthony gave the Knicks a 105-103 lead on a 13-foot basket
in the first overtime with 1:01 left. Nene Hilario tied the game
with two free throws with nine seconds remaining.  Gallinari had 11 rebounds and Harrington came off the bench
to score 24 points and grab 11 rebounds.  Anthony had 25 points and 10 rebounds, while  Landry Fields 
and Iman Shumpert had 18 points each for the Knicks.  The Nuggets (12-5) are in second place in the Western
Conference’s five-team Northwest Division, 1 ½ games behind
Oklahoma City (13-3). The Knicks (6-10) are five games behind
the leading Philadelphia 76ers (11-5) in the five-team Atlantic
Division of the Eastern Conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
